The S&P 500 and Dow Jones Industrial Average both reached new intraday record highs as trade fears eased and Treasury yields increased. The S&P 500 rose 0.6%, led by a 1.2% increase in materials and a 1% rise in financials. However, utilities declined by 0.9%. The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 0.8%, reaching a new record high. The Nasdaq Composite also climbed 0.5%, while the Russell 2000 index of small-cap stocks rose 0.4%.